From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: NanoPi K1 Plus OpenWrt project <noreply@example.invalid>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] rtl8189es: keep K1 Plus package default inert

The rtl8189es package default script still carries legacy behavior from older
wifi stacks: it patches shell-based mac80211 setup and force-raises wlan0.
On the current stack that makes K1 Plus first boot depend on a late
board-specific uci-defaults rewrite, which in practice turns the initial boot
sequence into a two-stage recovery dance.

Keep the kernel package default inert again and let the shared wifi config
generator own K1 Plus radio creation directly.

---
 package/kernel/rtl8189es/files/50_rtl-wifi | 7 +++----
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/package/kernel/rtl8189es/files/50_rtl-wifi b/package/kernel/rtl8189es/files/50_rtl-wifi
index 111111111111..222222222222 100644
--- a/package/kernel/rtl8189es/files/50_rtl-wifi
+++ b/package/kernel/rtl8189es/files/50_rtl-wifi
@@ -1,6 +1,5 @@
 #!/bin/sh
-
-sed -i '/iw dev "$wdev" del/d' /lib/netifd/wireless/mac80211.sh
-ip link set dev wlan0 up
-
+
+# NanoPi K1 Plus relies on the shared wifi generator instead of package-local
+# rtl8189es boot mutations.
 exit 0
